{
  "openapi": "3.1.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "Bike4Mind API",
    "version": "3.0.0",
    "description": "Programmatic access to the Bike4Mind API. Schemas are generated from the same Zod definitions that validate requests at runtime, so this spec cannot drift from the implementation.\n\n## Authentication\nSend an API key as `Authorization: Bearer b4m_live_<key>` (canonical), `x-api-key: b4m_live_<key>` (legacy), or `Authorization: ApiKey b4m_live_<key>`. A JWT access token is also accepted in the `Authorization: Bearer` header.\n\n## Scopes\nAPI keys carry `resource:action` scopes. The canonical set (from the runtime `ApiKeyScope` enum) is:\n- `notebooks:read`\n- `notebooks:write`\n- `files:read`\n- `files:write`\n- `ai:generate`\n- `ai:chat`\n- `projects:read`\n- `projects:write`\n- `cc-bridge:connect`\n- `admin:*`\n- `marketing-reports:read`\n- `marketing-reports:write`\n- `overwatch-ingest:write`\n- `embed:chat`\n\nPer-operation required scopes are published on each operation via the `x-required-scopes` extension.\n\n## CORS\nThe spec (`/api/v1/openapi.json`) is served publicly with permissive CORS. The API endpoints themselves are called server-to-server with a secret key and are not intended for browser CORS use.\n\n## Correlation\nEvery response carries an `X-Request-ID` header (echoed as `request_id`/`requestId` in bodies and events) for log correlation.",
    "contact": {
      "name": "Bike4Mind",
      "url": "https://your-deployment.example.com"
    },
    "license": {
      "name": "Proprietary"
    }
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "https://your-deployment.example.com",
      "description": "Production"
    },
    {
      "url": "https://staging.your-deployment.example.com",
      "description": "Staging"
    },
    {
      "url": "http://localhost:3000",
      "description": "Local dev"
    }
  ],
  "components": {
    "securitySchemes": {
      "bearerAuth": {
        "type": "http",
        "scheme": "bearer",
        "description": "Canonical auth. Send `Authorization: Bearer b4m_live_<key>`. A JWT access token is also accepted in this header; a token beginning with `b4m_` is treated as an API key, anything else as a JWT."
      },
      "apiKeyAuth": {
        "type": "apiKey",
        "in": "header",
        "name": "x-api-key",
        "description": "Legacy auth. Send `x-api-key: b4m_live_<key>`. Equivalent to `bearerAuth` for API keys."
      }
    },
